# Held-out IBT manifest -- physics-rebuild plan, PLAN.md Section 7.
#
# Manifest version: 2 (2026-05-23). Replace held-out rows over time with
# converged-fast setups the driver validates on track -- outlier setups
# (current H1-H5) measure corpus properties, not algorithm quality.
# Update this file + re-run `scripts/verify_holdout.sh` when rotating.
#
# Format: <sha256>  <path>  # <label> (<bytes>)
#
# These five IBTs are reserved for gate validation. They MUST NOT be loaded
# into any fit, train, or recommend pipeline. The catalog's `held_out=1`
# flag (set by Day 0 prep) makes `query_sessions(... include_held_out=False)`
# skip them; this manifest is the file-level integrity check.
#
# scripts/verify_holdout.sh re-hashes the listed paths against this manifest
# and FAILS if any has changed. Run it as part of every day's pre-work
# checklist (PLAN.md Section 8.1).
#
# Each session_id below is the first 16 hex chars of the SHA-256 of the
# corresponding IBT (the project's filename-independent session-id rule).

